If you are defeated once and tell yourself you will overcome, but carry on as
before, know in the end you'll be so ill and weakened that eventually you won't
even notice your mistake and will begin to rationalize your behavior.

  -- Epictetus, "Discourses," 2.18.31
%
Throw out your conceited opinions, for it is impossible for a person to begin to
learn what he thinks he already knows.

  -- Epictetus, "Discourses," 2.17.1
%
Remember, it is not enough to be hit or insulted to be harmed, you must believe
that you are being harmed. If someone succeeds in provoking you, realize that
your mind is complicit in the provocation. Which is why it is essential that we
not respond impulsively to impressions; take a moment before reacting, and you
will find it easier to maintain control.

  -- Epictetus, "The Art of Living"
